        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">D. Appleton &amp; Co. | 549 &amp; 551 Broadway, N.Y.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Nov 5 1874</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>Your favor of the 5<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. in which you refer to a new edition of y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. “Descent of of Man” is at hand.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>We shall be very glad to receive stereotype plates of the work, including wood cuts, and pay M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Murray 50£ for the casts—<ref target="#foot.f3"/> Some of the stereotypes of the cuts of the last edition were poorly done rendering quite difficult to print. Will you please bring this to the notice of M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Murray &amp; we have no doubt it will be corrected in future. We are desirous of receiving the plates as soon as possible as the present edition is exhausted. They may be delivered to our agency 16 Little Britain &amp; they will be forwarded to us.<ref target="#foot.f4"/></p>
<p>Your proposed work on ‘Carnivorous Plants’ we also desire to receive on the same terms.<ref target="#foot.f5"/> We are happy to say that your works continue to have good sale.</p>
<p>With thanks for yr kind expressions we remain | very sincerely yours | D Appleton &amp; Coy <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/></p>
<p rend="left">Charles Darwin Esq</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The date is established by the relationship between this letter, the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-9713.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to D. Appleton &amp; Co., 5 November 1874</ref>, and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-9741.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to G. H. Darwin, 2 December [1874]</ref>. The writer must have put ‘Nov 5’ in error.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-9713.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to D. Appleton &amp; Co., 5 November 1874</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">John Murray was CD’s publisher. The second US edition of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1966.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi></ref> was published in 1875. See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-9713.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to D. Appleton &amp; Co., 5 November 1874</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">Little Britain is a street in the City of London that was dominated by booksellers; Appletons had an agency at no. 16.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f5">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-9713.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to D. Appleton &amp; Co., 5 November 1874</ref> and n. 3.</note>
